The Omega name was an attempt to find a middle ground between the actual use of the greek alphabet poetically, with Omega representing , being at the end of the article, and the end of the series of univeres leading to the end, and the actual use of Omega in ordinal arithmetic were it is the first infinite cardinal/ordinal.

Fun fact: the spot in the series of ordinals I am referencing here is not actual epsilon, but a much smaller one: the Church-Kleene Ordinal, which is the smallest non-recursive ordinal, and the set of all recursive ordinals. Hence it being a 







